{"type":"message","id":"0f10f8f8","parentId":"36640e34","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:11:29.793Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pjfj5j6xhf0m_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 161011\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 IN PROGRESS: Compression primitives - CFI analysis complete, next is conditional content analysis\r\n- The highest priority pending experiment is **Conditional Content Analysis**\r\n\r\nThe experiment design:\r\n- For moderate-frequency tokens (freq=60-80%), split pulse pairs into T-present and T-absent groups\r\n- Question: does research content of next-pulse differ between groups?\r\n- Candidate tokens: \"compression\" (freq=199, CFI=0.995), \"causal\" (freq=162, CFI=0.981), \"phase\" (freq=187, CFI=0.946)\r\n- If no difference: CFI measures scaffolding. If yes: tokens are genuinely causal.\r\n- This distinguishes Pattern Information from Causal Information empirically\r\n\r\nThe most recent pulse is `pulse_2026-03-24_160909.md`.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Read the recent pulse file to understand the content\r\n2. Read the prior pulses to compare content when certain tokens are present vs absent\r\n3. Design and implement the conditional content analysis\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the research directory and state directory to understand the data available.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1's immediate next task is Conditional Content Analysis - the empirical test to distinguish Pattern Information (CFI) from Causal Information. This is the experiment that will determine whether high-CFI tokens like \"compression\" and \"causal\" are genuinely causal or just scaffolding.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a new analysis document for the Conditional Content Analysis experiment, implementing the empirical test on existing pulse data to compare next-pulse content when specific tokens are present vs absent.\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Conditional Content Analysis Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24 1630  \r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS  \r\n**Priority:** HIGHEST - Phase 1 completion dependency\r\n\r\n## Research Question\r\nDoes removing token T from state hurt prediction quality?\r\n\r\nSpecifically: When token T appears in pulse N, does pulse N+1 differ meaningfully in research content compared to when T does NOT appear?\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n- **If no difference:** CFI measures scaffolding/format patterns, not causation\r\n- **If yes:** Tokens are genuinely causal (they shape subsequent research direction)\r\n\r\n## Candidate Tokens for Testing\r\n\r\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Reason Selected |\r\n|-------|------|-----|-----------------|\r\n| compression | 199 | 0.995 | Core research topic, near-constant |\r\n| causal | 162 | 0.981 | Central concept in Phase 1 |\r\n| phase | 187 | 0.946 | Research trajectory marker |\r\n| breakthrough | 89 | 0.912 | Moderate freq - good test case |\r\n| experiment | 124 | 0.934 | Research activity marker |\r\n\r\n## Experimental Design\r\n\r\n### Method\r\n1. Load all pulse pairs (pulse_N, pulse_N+1)\r\n2. For each candidate token T:\r\n   - Group A: pairs where T appears in pulse_N\r\n   - Group B: pairs where T does NOT appear in pulse_N\r\n3. Compare Group A vs Group B on pulse_N+1 content:\r\n   - Topic modeling (what concepts appear)\r\n   - Research depth (new discoveries vs repetition)\r\n   - Action orientation (new experiments vs status quo)\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Topic Jaccard:** J(accident_topic_A, accident_topic_B)\r\n- **Novelty delta:** |Group A novelty| - |Group B novelty|\r\n- **Action delta:** new action count difference\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n- Constant-format tokens (freq=200): NO difference (they're scaffolding)\r\n- Causal tokens (freq 60-120): SHOULD see difference if truly causal\r\n- This empirically distinguishes Layer 1 (compression) from Layer 2 (causation)\r\n\r\n## Files Required\r\n- `state/pulses/` - all pulse markdown files\r\n- Token frequency data from prior CFI analysis\r\n\r\n## Status Log\r\n- 2026-03-24 1630: Experiment document created\r\n- 2026-03-24 1630: Awaiting pulse corpus analysis\r\nfile: research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 16:10:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774383089768}}
