{"type":"message","id":"8d78e01b","parentId":"f6c70ea3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:11:34.268Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3sjhc0i9aoam_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 161112\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 1 IN PROGRESS: Compression primitives\r\n- CFI analysis complete, next is conditional content analysis\r\n- The core breakthrough documents the difference between CFI (Pattern Information) and Causal Discovery (Transfer Entropy)\r\n- The immediate next experiment is \"Conditional Content Analysis\" - testing whether moderate-frequency tokens are genuinely causal\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to run the Conditional Content Analysis experiment. This involves:\r\n1. For moderate-frequency tokens (freq=60-80%), split pulse pairs into T-present and T-absent groups\r\n2. Compare research content of next-pulse between groups\r\n3. This distinguishes Pattern Information from Causal Information empirically\r\n\r\nGiven the goals, I should advance this experiment. Looking at the state, I need to:\r\n\r\n1. Run the conditional content analysis on recent pulses\r\n2. This would require analyzing pulse pairs to see if presence/absence of a token changes the next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available. The pulse script and recent pulses are in the sandbox. I should:\r\n1. Review the pulse log structure\r\n2. Implement the conditional content analysis\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to:\r\n- Run a script that extracts pulse pairs and analyzes conditional content\r\n- Or create a document outlining the analysis methodology and initial results\r\n\r\nGiven the stateless nature and the need for empirical evidence about whether tokens are causal vs just predictive, the Conditional Content Analysis is the key next step.\r\n\r\nLet me implement this analysis. I'll need to:\r\n1. Load the pulse log (recent pulses)\r\n2. For each candidate token, split pulses into T-present and T-absent groups\r\n3. Compare the subsequent pulse content between groups\r\n4. Document findings\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete action that advances the Phase 1 goals.\r\n\r\nLet me write the analysis as a document in the research folder.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1's Conditional Content Analysis is the critical next experiment to distinguish CFI (predictive pattern) from true causal tokens. Recent pulse logs are available to run this analysis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run the conditional content analysis on pulse pairs, testing whether tokens like \"compression\", \"causal\", and \"phase\" show different next-pulse content when present vs absent. This empirically tests the CFI≠causal distinction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Conditional Content Analysis\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24 1630  \r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n- Tokens with high CFI (≥0.9) but moderate frequency (60-120 range) may be:\r\n  - **Scaffolding**: Perfectly predictable but carry no causal weight\r\n  - **Genuinely causal**: Presence changes next-pulse research trajectory\r\n\r\n## Candidate Tokens\r\n\r\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Category |\r\n|-------|------|-----|----------|\r\n| compression | 199 | 0.995 | High freq, very high CFI |\r\n| causal | 162 | 0.981 | Moderate-high freq, very high CFI |\r\n| phase | 187 | 0.946 | High freq, high CFI |\r\n| cfi | 114 | 0.969 | Mid freq, high CFI |\r\n| strategy | 95 | 0.953 | Mid freq, high CFI |\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\nFor each token T, split pulse pairs into:\r\n- **T-present**: pulses containing T\r\n- **T-absent**: pulses NOT containing T\r\n\r\nCompare next-pulse content between groups:\r\n- Topic distribution\r\n- Research direction changes\r\n- Action frequency\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcomes\r\n\r\n### If tokens are scaffolding (CFI only):\r\n- Next-pulse content statistically identical regardless of T presence\r\n- Tokens are constant-format artifacts encoded in state\r\n\r\n### If tokens are genuinely causal:\r\n- T-present group shows different next-pulse trajectories\r\n- Specific research directions correlate with T presence\r\n\r\n## Analysis Script\r\nSee `analysis/conditional_content.ps1`\r\n```\r\nfile: research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 16:11:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774383094266}}
